Defendant in custody.
On counts 1, 3 and 4, three counts burglary, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seven (7) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by four (4) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent and concurrent with the sentence presently being served in Kewaunee County.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain fulltime employment;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
